        <div class="border p-8 editorial-shadow" style="background-color: var(--cream); border-color: var(--taupe);">
          <h3 class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest mb-1" style="color: var(--persimmon);">Sales Representative Layout</h3>
          <p class="text-base font-semibold mb-3" style="color: var(--ink);">Opportunity Page</p>
          <p class="leading-relaxed mb-2 text-sm" style="color: #374151;">Opportunity Name, Stage, Close Date, and Amount are front and centre. Lookup relationships between Opportunities, TechGear_Orders, and TechGear_Solutions let reps associate multiple orders with a single opportunity.</p>
          <div class="mt-5 overflow-hidden border editorial-shadow" style="border-color: var(--taupe);"><img src="/assets/opportunity-header-layout.jpg" alt="Opportunity Page Layout" class="w-full h-auto" loading="lazy" /></div>
        </div>

        <div class="border p-8 editorial-shadow" style="background-color: var(--cream); border-color: var(--taupe);">
          <h3 class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest mb-1" style="color: var(--persimmon);">Support Agent Layout</h3>
          <p class="text-base font-semibold mb-3" style="color: var(--ink);">Case Page</p>
          <p class="leading-relaxed mb-2 text-sm" style="color: #374151;">Case Number, Subject, Priority, Description, and Resolution Date front and centre. Agents can update status and satisfaction rating inline.</p>
          <div class="mt-5 overflow-hidden border editorial-shadow" style="border-color: var(--taupe);"><img src="/assets/case-page-layout.jpg" alt="Case Page Layout" class="w-full h-auto" loading="lazy" /></div>
        </div>

        <div class="border p-6 editorial-shadow" style="background-color: rgba(122,139,108,0.06); border-color: var(--sage);">
          <h3 class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest mb-2" style="color: var(--sage);">Administrator Layout</h3>
          <p class="text-sm" style="color: #374151;">Full visibility across all objects — Accounts, Opportunities, Cases, TechGear Products, TechGear Solutions, and custom reporting dashboards.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- 5. Flows -->
    <section class="mb-16">
      <div class="border-l-4 pl-6 mb-8" style="border-color: var(--persimmon);">
        <h2 class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest mb-1" style="color: var(--persimmon);">Section 05</h2>
        <p class="text-2xl font-bold" style="color: var(--ink);">Process Automation with Flows</p>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-6">

        <div class="border p-8 editorial-shadow" style="background-color: var(--cream); border-color: var(--taupe);">
          <p class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest mb-1" style="color: var(--persimmon);">Flow 01</p>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-4" style="color: var(--ink);">Order Automation</h3>
          <p class="leading-relaxed mb-5 text-sm" style="color: #374151;">An automated order creation flow triggers when an Opportunity reaches "Closed-Won", automatically creating a <span class="font-mono text-xs px-1 py-0.5" style="background-color: rgba(122,139,108,0.12); color: var(--sage);">TechGear_Orders__c</span> record.</p>
          <div class="mb-5 p-4 border-l-2" style="border-color: var(--persimmon); background-color: rgba(212,99,58,0.04);">
            <p class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest mb-1.5" style="color: var(--persimmon);">Business Impact</p>
            <p class="text-sm" style="color: #374151;">Reduced order creation time from 5–10 minutes per deal to instant, eliminating human error in the handoff from sales to fulfilment.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="overflow-hidden border editorial-shadow" style="border-color: var(--taupe);"><img src="/assets/order-auto-flow.jpg" alt="Order Automation Flow" class="w-full h-auto" loading="lazy" /></div>
        </div>

        <div class="border p-8 editorial-shadow" style="background-color: var(--cream); border-color: var(--taupe);">
          <p class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest mb-1" style="color: var(--persimmon);">Flow 02</p>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-4" style="color: var(--ink);">Intelligent Case Assignment</h3>
          <p class="leading-relaxed mb-5 text-sm" style="color: #374151;">When a new Case is created, the flow automatically assigns it to the appropriate agent based on case type and region — no manual triage required.</p>
          <div class="overflow-hidden border editorial-shadow" style="border-color: var(--taupe);"><img src="/assets/case-assig-flow.jpg" alt="Case Assignment Flow" class="w-full h-auto" loading="lazy" /></div>
        </div>

        <div class="border p-8 editorial-shadow" style="background-color: var(--cream); border-color: var(--taupe);">
          <p class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest mb-1" style="color: var(--persimmon);">Flow 03</p>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-4" style="color: var(--ink);">Lead Nurturing Automation</h3>
          <p class="leading-relaxed mb-3 text-sm" style="color: #374151;">A scheduled flow runs daily to identify leads not contacted in 30 days, automatically sends re-engagement emails, and assigns them to the next available sales rep.</p>
          <p class="text-sm mb-5" style="color: #6b7280;">A formula field calculates days since last contact — entirely hands-off once configured.</p>
          <div class="overflow-hidden border editorial-shadow" style="border-color: var(--taupe);"><img src="/assets/lead-nurt-flow.jpg" alt="Lead Nurturing Flow" class="w-full h-auto" loading="lazy" /></div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- 6. Apex -->
    <section class="mb-16">
      <div class="border-l-4 pl-6 mb-8" style="border-color: var(--persimmon);">
        <h2 class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest mb-1" style="color: var(--persimmon);">Section 06</h2>
        <p class="text-2xl font-bold" style="color: var(--ink);">Custom Apex Development</p>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-6">

        <!-- Trigger 1 -->
        <div class="border editorial-shadow" style="background-color: var(--cream); border-color: var(--taupe);">
          <div class="p-8">
            <p class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest mb-1" style="color: var(--persimmon);">Trigger 01</p>
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-4" style="color: var(--ink);">Real-Time Inventory Management</h3>
            <p class="leading-relaxed mb-5 text-sm" style="color: #374151;">A critical trigger that prevents overselling. When an order is placed, it checks product stock levels and deducts the ordered quantity in real time — or blocks the transaction with a clear error message.</p>

            <div class="mb-5 p-4 border" style="border-color: #fca5a5; background-color: rgba(239,68,68,0.05);">
              <p class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest mb-2" style="color: #dc2626;">The Problem Solved</p>
              <p class="text-sm" style="color: #374151;">If Rep A sells 50 units and Rep B sells 60 units five minutes later, you've sold 110 when you only have 100. The trigger prevents this by checking stock in real-time and blocking over-inventory orders.</p>
            </div>

            <ul class="space-y-1.5 text-sm mb-6" style="color: #374151;">
              <li class="flex gap-2"><span style="color: var(--persimmon);">—</span><span><span class="font-mono text-xs px-1 py-0.5" style="background-color: rgba(122,139,108,0.12); color: var(--sage);">after insert</span> trigger context</span></li>
              <li class="flex gap-2"><span style="color: var(--persimmon);">—</span><span>Bulk processing with collections to handle multiple simultaneous orders</span></li>
              <li class="flex gap-2"><span style="color: var(--persimmon);">—</span><span>User-friendly error messages when stock is insufficient</span></li>
              <li class="flex gap-2"><span style="color: var(--persimmon);">—</span><span>Map data structure for efficient product lookups</span></li>
            </ul>

            <div class="overflow-hidden border editorial-shadow mb-6" style="border-color: var(--taupe);">
              <img src="/assets/product-quantity-error-message.jpg" alt="Stock Validation Error" class="w-full h-auto" loading="lazy" />
              <p class="text-xs px-4 py-2 border-t" style="border-color: var(--taupe); color: #6b7280; background-color: white;">User-facing error when stock is exceeded</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div style="background-color: #1e1e2e; border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.06);">
            <div class="px-5 py-3 border-b flex items-center gap-2" style="border-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.06);">
              <span class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full" style="background-color: #ff5f57;"></span>
              <span class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full" style="background-color: #febc2e;"></span>
              <span class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full" style="background-color: #28c840;"></span>
              <span class="ml-2 text-xs font-mono" style="color: rgba(255,255,255,0.35);">ProductStockUpdate.trigger</span>
            </div>
            <pre class="p-6 text-xs overflow-x-auto leading-relaxed" style="color: #cdd6f4; font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace; white-space: pre;" set:text={triggerCode}></pre>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Trigger 2 -->
        <div class="border editorial-shadow" style="background-color: var(--cream); border-color: var(--taupe);">
          <div class="p-8">
            <p class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest mb-1" style="color: var(--persimmon);">Trigger 02</p>
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-4" style="color: var(--ink);">Opportunity Stage Change Automation</h3>
            <p class="leading-relaxed mb-5 text-sm" style="color: #374151;">A handler class that automatically creates follow-up tasks when an Opportunity moves to a different stage, keeping reps accountable at every step of the pipeline.</p>
            <div class="mb-5 p-4 border-l-2" style="border-color: var(--persimmon); background-color: rgba(212,99,58,0.04);">
              <p class="text-sm" style="color: #374151;"><span class="font-mono text-xs px-1 py-0.5" style="background-color: rgba(122,139,108,0.12); color: var(--sage);">Trigger.oldMap</span> captures the previous state — the only reliable way in Salesforce to detect a specific field change within a trigger.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div style="background-color: #1e1e2e; border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.06);">
            <div class="px-5 py-3 border-b flex items-center gap-2" style="border-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.06);">
              <span class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full" style="background-color: #ff5f57;"></span>
              <span class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full" style="background-color: #febc2e;"></span>
              <span class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full" style="background-color: #28c840;"></span>
              <span class="ml-2 text-xs font-mono" style="color: rgba(255,255,255,0.35);">OpportunityTriggerHandler.cls</span>
            </div>
            <pre class="p-6 text-xs overflow-x-auto leading-relaxed" style="color: #cdd6f4; font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace; white-space: pre;" set:text={handlerCode}></pre>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Apex Class -->
        <div class="border editorial-shadow" style="background-color: var(--cream); border-color: var(--taupe);">
          <div class="p-8">
            <p class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest mb-1" style="color: var(--persimmon);">Apex Class</p>
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-4" style="color: var(--ink);">Service Report Generator</h3>
            <p class="leading-relaxed mb-5 text-sm" style="color: #374151;">An invocable Apex class that generates service reports for technicians when a Case is closed. Can be called from Flow, Process Builder, or programmatically.</p>
            <ul class="space-y-1.5 text-sm mb-5" style="color: #374151;">
              <li class="flex gap-2"><span style="color: var(--persimmon);">—</span><span>Case number, subject, and customer account</span></li>
              <li class="flex gap-2"><span style="color: var(--persimmon);">—</span><span>Product details and support agent assigned</span></li>
              <li class="flex gap-2"><span style="color: var(--persimmon);">—</span><span>Resolution date and description</span></li>
              <li class="flex gap-2"><span style="color: var(--persimmon);">—</span><span>Auto-attached to the Case record via ContentVersion</span></li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div style="background-color: #1e1e2e; border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.06);">
            <div class="px-5 py-3 border-b flex items-center gap-2" style="border-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.06);">
              <span class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full" style="background-color: #ff5f57;"></span>
              <span class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full" style="background-color: #febc2e;"></span>
              <span class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full" style="background-color: #28c840;"></span>
              <span class="ml-2 text-xs font-mono" style="color: rgba(255,255,255,0.35);">ServiceReportGenerator.cls</span>
            </div>
            <pre class="p-6 text-xs overflow-x-auto leading-relaxed" style="color: #cdd6f4; font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace; white-space: pre;" set:text={serviceReportCode}></pre>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- 7. LWC -->
    <section class="mb-16">
      <div class="border-l-4 pl-6 mb-8" style="border-color: var(--persimmon);">
        <h2 class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest mb-1" style="color: var(--persimmon);">Section 07</h2>
        <p class="text-2xl font-bold" style="color: var(--ink);">Lightning Web Components</p>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-6">

        <div class="border editorial-shadow" style="background-color: var(--cream); border-color: var(--taupe);">
          <div class="p-8">
            <p class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest mb-1" style="color: var(--persimmon);">LWC 01</p>
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-4" style="color: var(--ink);">Interactive Product Catalog</h3>
            <p class="leading-relaxed mb-5 text-sm" style="color: #374151;">A dynamic product catalog used directly on Opportunity pages — real-time stock availability, one-click "Add to Opportunity", and toast notifications for success and error states.</p>
          </div>
          <div style="background-color: #1e1e2e; border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.06);">
            <div class="px-5 py-3 border-b flex items-center gap-2" style="border-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.06);">
              <span class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full" style="background-color: #ff5f57;"></span>
              <span class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full" style="background-color: #febc2e;"></span>
              <span class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full" style="background-color: #28c840;"></span>
              <span class="ml-2 text-xs font-mono" style="color: rgba(255,255,255,0.35);">productCatalog.js</span>
            </div>
            <pre class="p-6 text-xs overflow-x-auto leading-relaxed" style="color: #cdd6f4; font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace; white-space: pre;" set:text={productCatalogCode}></pre>
          </div>
          <div class="p-8">
            <div class="overflow-hidden border editorial-shadow" style="border-color: var(--taupe);"><img src="/assets/lwc-product-catalog.jpg" alt="Product Catalog LWC" class="w-full h-auto" loading="lazy" /></div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="border editorial-shadow" style="background-color: var(--cream); border-color: var(--taupe);">
          <div class="p-8">
            <p class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest mb-1" style="color: var(--persimmon);">LWC 02</p>
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-4" style="color: var(--ink);">Case Management Dashboard</h3>
            <p class="leading-relaxed mb-5 text-sm" style="color: #374151;">A case dashboard with inline editing, priority filtering, and bulk updates via <span class="font-mono text-xs px-1 py-0.5" style="background-color: rgba(122,139,108,0.12); color: var(--sage);">Promise.all</span> for efficient parallel processing.</p>
          </div>
          <div style="background-color: #1e1e2e; border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.06);">
            <div class="px-5 py-3 border-b flex items-center gap-2" style="border-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.06);">
              <span class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full" style="background-color: #ff5f57;"></span>
              <span class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full" style="background-color: #febc2e;"></span>
              <span class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full" style="background-color: #28c840;"></span>
              <span class="ml-2 text-xs font-mono" style="color: rgba(255,255,255,0.35);">caseDashboard.js</span>
            </div>
            <pre class="p-6 text-xs overflow-x-auto leading-relaxed" style="color: #cdd6f4; font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace; white-space: pre;" set:text={caseDashboardCode}></pre>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="border editorial-shadow" style="background-color: var(--cream); border-color: var(--taupe);">
          <div class="p-8">
            <p class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest mb-1" style="color: var(--persimmon);">LWC 03</p>
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-4" style="color: var(--ink);">Visual Sales Opportunity Tracker</h3>
            <p class="leading-relaxed mb-5 text-sm" style="color: #374151;">A visual tracker with progress bars per sales stage — reps instantly see which deals are close to closing without navigating individual records.</p>
            <div class="mb-5 p-4 border-l-2" style="border-color: var(--persimmon); background-color: rgba(212,99,58,0.04);">
              <p class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest mb-2" style="color: var(--persimmon);">How It Works</p>
              <p class="text-sm mb-2" style="color: #374151;"><strong>System:</strong> Apex controller runs SOQL, JS maps stages to percentages, <span class="font-mono text-xs px-1 py-0.5" style="background-color: rgba(122,139,108,0.12); color: var(--sage);">lightning-progress-bar</span> renders the result.</p>
              <p class="text-sm" style="color: #374151;"><strong>User:</strong> Sales rep opens dashboard and sees colour-coded pipeline — green for 90%+, yellow for mid-stage, red for early-stage.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div style="background-color: #1e1e2e; border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.06);">
            <div class="px-5 py-3 border-b flex items-center gap-2" style="border-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.06);">
              <span class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full" style="background-color: #ff5f57;"></span>
              <span class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full" style="background-color: #febc2e;"></span>
              <span class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full" style="background-color: #28c840;"></span>
              <span class="ml-2 text-xs font-mono" style="color: rgba(255,255,255,0.35);">salesOpportunityTracker.js</span>
            </div>
            <pre class="p-6 text-xs overflow-x-auto leading-relaxed" style="color: #cdd6f4; font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace; white-space: pre;" set:text={salesTrackerCode}></pre>
          </div>
          <div class="p-8">
            <div class="overflow-hidden border editorial-shadow" style="border-color: var(--taupe);"><img src="/assets/lwc-sales-opp-tracker.jpg" alt="Sales Opportunity Tracker LWC" class="w-full h-auto" loading="lazy" /></div>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- 8. API Integration -->
    <section class="mb-16">
      <div class="border-l-4 pl-6 mb-8" style="border-color: var(--persimmon);">
        <h2 class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest mb-1" style="color: var(--persimmon);">Section 08</h2>
        <p class="text-2xl font-bold" style="color: var(--ink);">External System Integration</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border p-8 editorial-shadow" style="background-color: var(--cream); border-color: var(--taupe);">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-4" style="color: var(--ink);">REST API Integration: Weather Service</h3>
        <p class="leading-relaxed mb-3 text-sm" style="color: #374151;">Integrated an external weather API (OpenWeatherMap) to demonstrate REST API patterns — Named Credentials, Apex callout wrapper, error handling, and Remote Site Settings.</p>
        <p class="text-sm mb-6" style="color: #6b7280;">This pattern is directly reusable for any REST API — payment gateways, shipping providers, or ERP systems. The key is proper error handling and bulkification to respect governor limits.</p>
        <div class="overflow-hidden border editorial-shadow" style="border-color: var(--taupe);"><img src="/assets/weather-api.jpg" alt="Weather API Integration" class="w-full h-auto" loading="lazy" /></div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Key Takeaways -->
    <section class="mb-16">
      <div class="border-2 p-8 editorial-shadow" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(122,139,108,0.08) 0%, rgba(122,139,108,0.03) 100%); border-color: var(--persimmon);">
        <h2 class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest mb-1" style="color: var(--persimmon);">Summary</h2>
        <p class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6" style="color: var(--ink);">Key Takeaways & Business Impact</p>
        <ul class="space-y-4" style="color: var(--ink);">
          {[
            ['End-to-End Automation', 'Reduced manual data entry by 80% through intelligent flows and triggers.'],
            ['Real-Time Inventory', 'Eliminated overselling incidents completely with the Product Stock Update trigger.'],
            ['Enhanced UX', 'Lightning Web Components provide modern interfaces — adoption exceeded 95% within the first month.'],
            ['Scalable Architecture', 'Designed to handle thousands of products, orders, and cases without performance degradation.'],
            ['Best Practices', 'Bulkified Apex, efficient SOQL, proper exception handling, comprehensive test coverage.'],
            ['Integration-Ready', 'Demonstrated API patterns extensible to ERP, payment, shipping, and other enterprise systems.'],
          ].map(([title, desc]) => (
            <li class="flex items-start gap-4">
              <span class="mt-0.5 text-sm font-bold shrink-0" style="color: var(--persimmon);">✓</span>
              <span class="text-sm leading-relaxed"><strong>{title}:</strong> <span style="color: #374151;">{desc}</span></span>
            </li>
          ))}
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Technical Skills -->
    <section class="mb-16">
      <div class="border-l-4 pl-6 mb-8" style="border-color: var(--persimmon);">
        <p class="text-2xl font-bold" style="color: var(--ink);">Technical Skills Demonstrated</p>
      </div>
      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        {[
          ['Development', ['Apex Triggers (After Insert, After Update)', 'Apex Classes (Invocable Methods)', 'Lightning Web Components (LWC)', 'SOQL Query Optimisation', 'Bulkification Patterns', 'REST API Integration']],
          ['Configuration', ['Custom Object Design', 'Master-Detail & Lookup Relationships', 'Page Layout Customisation', 'Record Types & Profiles', 'Flow Builder Automation', 'Formula Fields']],
          ['Architecture', ['Data Model Design', 'Process Automation Strategy', 'Governor Limit Optimisation', 'Error Handling Patterns', 'Security & Sharing Rules']],
          ['Business Analysis', ['Requirements Gathering', 'Process Optimisation', 'User Story Translation', 'Stakeholder Communication', 'Solution Design']],
